It is freezing today by the way so this is very appropriate.
顺便说一句，今天真是冷得要命，所以这个词很应景。

12
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:40,160
Freezing means very, very, very cold.
“Freezing”意思是极其、极其、极其冷。

13
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:41,800
Okay, it is freezing.
好的，就是冷得要命。

14
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,520
Okay, so it's very cold.
好的，所以非常冷。

15
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:45,040
It's freezing today.
今天冷得要命。

16
00:00:45,040 --> 00:00:50,280
It's so cold in fact you can't have water outside because the water will become ice.
实际上冷到你不能把水放在外面，因为水会变成冰。

17
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:51,280
It will freeze.
它会结冰。

18
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:53,040
Okay, great word.
好的，这个词很棒。

19
00:00:53,040 --> 00:01:02,600
So let's listen to our dialogue for the very first time.
那么让我们第一次听一下我们的对话。

20
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,600
It's freezing in here.
这里冷得要命。

21
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,400
Can I turn up the heat?
我能把暖气开大点吗？

22
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,160
Don't touch that thermostat.
别碰那个恒温器。

23
00:01:07,160 --> 00:01:08,720
You don't pay the bills around here.
这里又不是你付账单。

24
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,520
Dad, are you serious?
爸，你是认真的吗？

25
00:01:10,520 --> 00:01:13,800
What's the point of having central heating if we can't use it?
如果我们不能用中央供暖，那装它有什么用？

26
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:16,680
Look, I can see my breath.
看，我都能看到自己的呼吸了。

27
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:17,840
Put on a sweater.
穿上件毛衣。

28
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:21,560
I'm not going to let you run up my heating bill just because it's a bit chilly.
我不会因为有点凉就让你把我的取暖费账单搞上去。

29
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:24,160
Dad, I'm going to catch a cold.
爸，我会感冒的。

30
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:28,760
When I was your age, my parents didn't have central heating like you do.
我像你这么大的时候，我父母可没有像你这样的中央供暖。

31
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:31,960
We had a furnace in the center of the living room and that was it.
我们客厅中间只有一个炉子，就那样。

32
00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:35,600
We used it to cook, heat the house, and even dry our clothes.
我们用那个炉子做饭、取暖，甚至烘干衣服。

33
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,100
We never caught a cold.
我们从来没感冒过。

34
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,100
You should be grateful.
你应该知足了。

35
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:46,160
Alright, we're back and this is actually what a lot of dads are like I think around the
好的，我们回来了，这实际上就是很多爸爸的样子，我想全世界都差不多。

36
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:47,160
world.


37
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:50,840
Yep, my dad definitely liked to keep the heat low in the house.
是的，我爸爸绝对喜欢把家里的暖气调低。

38
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:55,880
Alright, so we'll talk about that a little bit later but let's take a look at some four
好的，我们稍后会再谈这个，但先来看看今天的“语言要点”中的四个词。

39
00:01:55,880 --> 00:02:00,440
words on Language Takeaway today.


40
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:01,440
Language Takeaway
语言要点

41
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:06,880
Well, this first word is important for anyone who has a home with heating.
嗯，第一个词对家里有暖气的人来说很重要。

42
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:07,880
It's called a thermostat.
它叫恒温器。

43
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,440
Alright, a thermostat.
好的，一个恒温器。

44
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,800
What is a thermostat?
什么是恒温器？

45
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:20,800
A thermostat is a dial or like a device on the wall that tells you how hot or how
恒温器是墙上的一种刻度盘或装置，用来显示温度高低。

46
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,800
cold the house is.
这房子真冷。

47
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:24,160
It's like a thermometer for your house.
它就像你家的温度计一样。

48
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:28,920
Okay, so you can move the thermostat, the temperature to make the house warmer or colder,
好的，你可以调节恒温器，也就是温度，让房子变得更暖或更冷。

49
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:29,920
right?
对吧？

50
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:34,800
Right, so if it says it's 20 degrees and I think that's too cold, I can turn the thermostat
好的，如果显示是20度，而我觉得太冷了，我可以调一下恒温器。

51
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:37,240
up to 23 degrees.
最高可达23度。

52
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:44,760
Alright, and well very much related to a thermostat and what this device does is our next word,
好的，这个词和我们刚才说的恒温器以及它的功能密切相关，这就是我们的下一个词。

53
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:45,760
central heating.
中央供暖。

54
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:48,280
Right, so if you have central heating, you have a thermostat.
对，所以如果你有中央供暖系统，你就会有恒温器。

55
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:54,320
It's the way to control the heat and central heating means that you have one heater for
这是控制温度的方式，中央供暖意味着你只有一个加热器。

56
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:58,880
the whole house and so the air comes into all the different rooms.
整个房子都是这样，所以空气能进入所有不同的房间。

57
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:04,840
So not many places in China have this but for example in the United States, in Canada,
所以在中国很多地方没有这个，但比如在美国、加拿大，

58
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:05,840
it is very common.
这很常见。

59
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:10,480
Okay, so your house or your apartment building will have central heating and then you can
好的，那么你的房子或公寓楼会有中央供暖系统，然后你就可以

60
00:03:10,480 --> 00:03:13,760
control how cold or warm the house is with thermostats.
用恒温器来控制房子的冷热。

61
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,760
Exactly.
没错。

62
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:20,080
Very good and well our next word is related to temperature and it's chilly.
很好。接下来这个词和温度有关，是“chilly”（寒冷的）。

63
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:26,200
Chilly, okay, so there's a big difference between chilly and freezing.
冷，好吧，所以“chilly”和“freezing”之间有很大的区别。

64
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:28,440
Freezing means very very very cold.
Freezing 意思是特别特别特别冷。

65
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,000
Chilly means a little cold.
Chilly 意思是有点冷。

66
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,840
Right, so it's a little cold.
对，是有点冷。

67
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,840
It's a bit chilly.
有点凉。

68
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,800
Right, so it's a bit chilly today, I'm going to wear a hat.
好的，今天有点冷，我打算戴顶帽子。

69
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:41,480
Okay, if it's freezing, I'm going to wear a hat and mittens and a scarf and coat and
好的，如果天寒地冻，我就戴上帽子、手套、围巾，再穿上大衣。

70
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,480
boots.
靴子。

71
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:48,160
Right, so if it's a bit chilly, it's not very cold and well moving on, the dad mentioned
好的，如果只是有点凉，那就不算很冷。好了，继续往下，爸爸提到了

72
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:52,160
about him having a furnace when he was young.
他年轻时家里有个火炉。

73
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:57,280
That's right, the dad had a furnace in his house and the furnace is a way to heat your
没错，这位爸爸家里有个火炉，火炉是用来取暖的。

74
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:58,280
house.
房子。

75
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,200
It's like a stove.
它就像个炉子。

76
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:02,760
So yeah, just consider it like a big oven, right?
所以，你就把它想象成一个巨大的烤箱，对吧？

77
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:06,680
Maybe you've seen it in the old movies where you would have to throw firewood into the
也许你在老电影里见过，得往里面扔柴火。

78
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,960
furnace to make it heat up the house.
让炉子给房子供暖。

79
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:15,400
Exactly, and so this is very common in older homes and not very common in apartments.
没错，这在老房子里很常见，但在公寓里就不太常见了。

80
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:20,360
Right, and well, that's all the words we have for language takeaway today.
好的，以上就是我们今天语言小课堂的全部词汇。

81
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:28,520
Why don't we listen to this chilly dialogue again.
我们为什么不重新听一遍这段冷飕飕的对话呢？

82
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:29,520
It's freezing in here.
这里冷死了。

83
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,320
Can I turn up the heat?
我能把暖气开大点吗？

84
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:33,100
Don't touch that thermostat.
别碰那个恒温器。

85
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,640
You don't pay the bills around here.
这儿又不是你付账单。

86
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:36,440
Dad, are you serious?
爸，你是认真的吗？

87
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:39,400
What's the point of having central heating if we can't use it?
有中央供暖却不能用，那还有什么意义？

88
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:42,600
Look, I can see my breath.
看，我都能看见自己呼出的气了。

89
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:43,720
Put on a sweater.
穿上件毛衣。

90
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:47,480
I'm not going to let you run up my heating bill just because it's a bit chilly.
我不会因为有点冷就让你把我的取暖费账单搞得老高。

91
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:50,080
Dad, I'm going to catch a cold.
爸，我会感冒的。

92
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:54,700
When I was your age, my parents didn't have central heating like you do.
我像你这么大的时候，我爸妈可没有你们现在这样的中央供暖。

93
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,880
We had a furnace in the center of the living room and that was it.
我们客厅中间只有一个炉子，就那样。

94
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:01,560
We used it to cook, heat the house, and even dry our clothes.
我们用那个炉子做饭、取暖，甚至烘干衣服。

95
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,040
We never caught a cold.
我们从没感冒过。

96
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:08,320
You should be grateful.
你应该知足了。

97
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,320
Alright we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

98
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:15,440
So now we have prepared for you three key phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在我们为你准备了流利度训练中的三个关键短语。

99
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,440
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

100
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:22,240
Okay, so this first phrase is related to thermostat.
好的，第一个短语和恒温器有关。

101
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:26,200
So thermostat like we said is like a thermometer but we can control the temperature.
恒温器就像温度计，但我们可以控制温度。

102
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:31,540
So if we want to make the temperature hotter, we turn up the thermostat.
所以如果我们想让温度更高，我们就调高恒温器。

103
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:35,200
So this is a phrasal verb, to turn up the heat.
这是一个动词短语，to turn up the heat（调高暖气）。

104
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,880
You could say this about heat.
你可以用这个来说暖气。

105
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,240
You could say this about noise too.
你也可以用这个来说噪音。

106
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,720
Can you turn up the radio?
你能把收音机开大点吗？

107
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,160
Turn up the volume.
把音量调大。

108
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,400
So it's to increase.
所以它的意思是增加。

109
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:46,080
To increase, to make bigger or warmer or louder.
增加，让东西变大、变暖或变响。

110
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:50,800
Alright and if we wanted to decrease the temperature in the thermostat, you would say...
好的，如果我们想降低恒温器的温度，你会说……

111
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,960
Turn down.
调低。

112
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:52,960
Turn down the heat.
把暖气调低。

113
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:53,960
Exactly.
没错。

114
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:54,960
So it's too hot in here.
所以这里太热了。

115
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,800
Can you please turn down the heat?
你能把暖气调低吗？

116
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,560
Alright, very good.
好的，非常好。

117
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:04,640
And our next phrase is, well the dad was talking about the bills and how expensive it is to
我们的下一个短语是，爸爸在谈论账单以及使用恒温器有多贵，

118
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:09,680
use the thermostat and he said, I'm not going to let you run up my heating bill.
他说，我不会让你把我的取暖费账单搞得老高。

119
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:12,520
Okay, so a bill is like you know, something that you pay.
好的，账单就像你要付的东西。

120
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:13,600
It's money.
是钱。

121
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,120
And so in this case, I don't want you to run up the bill.
所以在这种情况下，我不想让你把账单搞大。

122
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:20,360
That means to increase the amount of money I have to spend.
这意味着增加我必须支付的金额。

123
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:25,440
So maybe if you leave your television on all night, you're running up your electricity
所以如果你整晚开着电视，你就是在增加你的电费

124
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:26,440
bill.
账单。

125
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,440
Exactly.
没错。

126
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:30,840
And if you leave it on 10 hours a day, you run up the phone bill and your mother kills
如果你每天开10小时，你就是在增加电话费，然后你妈妈会杀了

127
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:31,840
you.
你。

128
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:32,840
Right.
对。

129
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:36,320
Alright and well the daughter was complaining about her catching a cold.
好的，女儿在抱怨她感冒了。

130
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:37,640
To catch a cold.
感冒。

131
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,920
Alright, so remember this.
好的，记住这个。

132
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:44,680
A cold is when you have maybe a runny nose and a cough and a sore throat.
感冒就是你可能流鼻涕、咳嗽和喉咙痛。

133
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:47,020
It usually happens when the weather changes.
通常发生在天气变化的时候。

134
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:48,600
But we don't get a cold.
但我们不说“得到感冒”。

135
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,600
You catch a cold.
而是说“染上感冒”。

136
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,600
Okay.
好的。

137
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,880
And remember like in baseball, you throw and catch.
记住，就像在棒球里，你投球和接球。

138
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:54,880
It's something that's fast.
这是很快的事情。

139
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,720
Alright, so you catch a cold.
好的，所以你说“染上感冒”。

140
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,720
What about the flu?
那流感呢？

141
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,400
Do you get the flu or catch the flu?
你是说“得到流感”还是“染上流感”？

142
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:02,580
So you can't catch a flu but you can catch a cold.
所以你不能说“染上流感”，但可以说“染上感冒”。

143
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:03,680
Just remember this phrase.
记住这个短语。

144
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:05,400
To catch a cold.
染上感冒。

145
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,000
I caught the cold.
我染上了感冒。

146
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,920
To catch a cold or I caught a cold.
染上感冒或我染上了感冒。

147
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:14,080
It's almost like if I have it, I can throw it to you Marco.
这就像如果我有，我可以把它扔给你，Marco。

148
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,080
Achoo!
阿嚏！

149
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:16,080
And you catch it.
然后你接住了它。

150
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,720
Right, because it's in the air, the virus.
对，因为病毒在空气中。

151
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:19,480
Yeah, it passes very quickly.
是的，它传播得很快。

152
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,560
Alright, very good.
好的，非常好。

153
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,240
So an interesting dialogue.
所以这是一个有趣的对话。

154
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:31,000
Let's listen to it one last time.
让我们最后听一遍。

155
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,000
It's freezing in here.
这里冷死了。

156
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,800
Can I turn up the heat?
我能把暖气开大点吗？

157
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,600
Don't touch that thermostat.
别碰那个恒温器。

158
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,160
You don't pay the bills around here.
这里不是你付账单。

159
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,920
Dad, are you serious?
爸，你是认真的吗？

160
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:42,200
What's the point of having central heating if we can't use it?
如果我们不能用中央供暖，那装它有什么用？

